comment: Pachulia (DAL) holds Marjanovic's (SAS) arms during the rebound.
Nowitzki (DAL) is assessed a Respect for the Game technical foul for comments directed at an official. All technical fouls are reviewed by Basketball Operations.
Nowitzki (DAL) makes incidental contact with Green (SAS) as the two players move up the court.

Matthews (DAL) establishes a position in Anderson's (SAS) path. Since Anderson is stationary and Matthews is in an area visible to him, Matthews does not need to give him any room to avoid the screen.
Miller (SAS) starts to exit the lane under three seconds but does not fully clear.
Green (SAS) makes contact with Williams (DAL) that affects his RSBQ.
Pachulia (DAL) sets the screen on Miller (SAS) and gives him room to avoid the contact.
Anderson (SAS) makes contact with Nowitzki's (DAL) body that affects his shot attempt.
Nowitzki (DAL) makes contact with Anderson (SAS) that affects his FOM away from the ball as he attempts to establish post position.
Nowitzki (DAL) makes incidental contact with Anderson (SAS) that does not affect his shot attempt.
Matthews (DAL) gets his hands on the ball and a jump ball is correctly called.
Williams (DAL) makes contact with Martin's (SAS) arm as he tries to secure the inbounds pass.
Green (SAS) makes incidental contact with Williams (DAL) that does not affect his RSBQ.
Williams (DAL) commits a take foul on Miller (SAS).
Miller (SAS) legally contests Felton's (DAL) jump shot attempt. Any "high-five" contact after the release is considered incidental.
Villanueva (DAL) makes contact with Anderson (SAS) after he secures the rebound.
